inn1.comm: starts with the sort of ball that inspired the famous Mitchell Johnson song about bowling to the left and bowling to the right, way outside off stump
this is the sort of ball that makes Mitchell Johnson such a dangerous bowler, a yorker swinging towards off stump that is squeezed out by Rohit
pitched up and outside off, crisply driven towards cover by Rohit
drops it shorter this time, above 90mph, just outside off, Rohit drops his wrists as he allows the ball through to the keeper
short and quick, 91.5mph, over the stumps, Rohit sways out of the line of that one
wide down the leg side
length ball on off stump, Rohit gets forward and defends
length ball on the pads, Rohit can't get bat on it, off the pads towards the leg side
starts with one down the leg side, off the pads and past Haddin for four leg-byes

what a shot to get off the mark with, hardly any follow-through as he punched that between mid-off and extra cover, not too much wrong with the delivery from McKay, the outfield is superfast here as well
swings and misses this time, a length ball outside off that Dhawan wants to sends through the cover, beaten
four more, this time there was plenty wrong with the delivery, on the pads with a packed off-side field, easily tucked to the square-leg boundary
just outside off stump, 133kph, left alone by Dhawan

Australia conceded 176 before getting their first wicket in the previous match, this time they get it much quicker, McKay has a knack for getting wickets, and he sends back Dhawan with a back of length ball angling across, Dhawan nicks it through to the keeper, there's a confident appeal, the umpire Shamsuddin was unmoved, but Dhawan had started to walk, it was only then that the umpire raised his finger
inside-edge and that rolls towards the off side
off the pads and behind square leg
short of length ball on off stump, defended solidly to the off side
full and wide outside off, 144.5kph, punched off bended knees towards point, cleanly hit but not placed well enough to beat point
good tight line from Johnson, keeps it on off stump, Kohli gets behind the line and defends
this was full and wide outside off and he safely leaves it alone
too wide outside the off stump and he leaves it alone
fullish in length on the off stump and he gets forward and defends
streaky! This one came back in very slightly and he reached out to drive and got an inside edge past the stumps, beats the keeper
this was a bit too wide and he cuts past backward point, third man was square and he cuts it off
this was far too full and wide outside off, Johnson lost control of that, had to lean a long way across and drive it past cover, good shot
this was class! Johnson aimed for the yorker, outside off, he only looked to dig it out and he middled it past cover point, raced away
keeps it outside off and he safely leaves it alone
this was close to the half volley and he mistimed it to the off side
keeps it outside off and moves away and he safely leaves it alone
solid in defense, he gets forward and defends
stays beside the line and steers it towards point
hits a good length on the off stump and he stays back and defends
drifts this back in on a fuller length and he looks to drive and mistimes it to the leg side
this was beside the line and he angles it to third man
lands it outside off and moves away, he leaves it alone
poor delivery, short and wide outside off, had to really reach out and carve it over cover point
starts with  a back of a length ball on off stump, 126kph, defended towards square leg
angling in towards middle and off, length ball is blocked down the track off the front foot
down the leg side, there were faint cries of 'catch it,' but only to perhaps distract the umpire from calling it a wide
short of length ball angling in, pushed towards midwicket
length ball just outside off, nudged towards midwicket for a quick single
shorter this time, stylishly pushed towards point

Watson gets a wicket in his first over, Rohit is gone cheaply, the short ball bounced more than Rohit expects, he goes for the pull but that is a top edge that swirls towards the keeper and slip, Aaron Finch takes the catch and Australia already have more wickets than they did in the Jaipur ODI
length ball heading for the pads, worked in front of square leg
that nips in a bit after pitching outside off, Kohli allows the ball through to the keeper and that ball wasn't too far from off stump
cracking shot from Kohli, lashes this through cover for four, showing the sort of form he is in
outside off, allows this one through to the keeper
shorter this time, Kohli pushes this back towards the bowler off the backfoot
well outside off, Kohli isn't interested in chasing that one this early in the innings
short and well outside off, reaches out and pokes that towards point
Watson tries the short stuff again, Kohli isn't afraid to pull, connects well and that is another boundary
superb timing there from Kohli to bring up India's 50, that was pitched up on the pads, whipped off the back foot in front of square leg for four more
short of length ball just outside off, drops it towards square leg and gets a quick single
well outside off, Raina happy to leave that to the keeper

Raina places this perfectly, waits on the back foot and punches this past point for another boundary, that was just in front of a diving backward point, an expensive over from Watson and a confidence-building shot for Raina
a glorious drive through cover from Kohli, holds the pose as well as he crunches that length ball through the off side, just past short cover
another dirve, this time short cover gets a hand on it, and it's only a single
defended towards the off side by Raina from the crease
pitched up and outside off, driven off the front foot towards mid-off
short of length ball on middle and leg, defends this towards mid-on
on the pads once more, Raina watchfully tucks this towards midwicket
Johnson returns with a 141kph delivery, pushed towards midwicket off the back foot
sprays this down the leg side, nearly 144kph that
back of length ball, 148.5kph, Raina was waiting on the back foot, looks to send that to the leg side but can't connect, he was looking to force that one, not just guide it
a leading edge this time, no real danger though it flies in the direction of cover, lands well short
looks cramped as he defends that off the back foot to the leg side
there's the Johnson short ball outside off, Raina was in no position to play the hook, he wafts at it (if an attempted hook can be called a waft), no connection
short of length ball form round the wicket, 147.8, Raina tucks this towards midwicket for a single
length ball on off stump from McKay, Raina gently pushes this towards mid-off and sets off for a well-judged single
length ball on legstump, clipped behind square leg
great-looking drive off the front foot from Raina, gets a good stride in as he punches that, can't beat the diving fielder at short cover
this time the placement is better, Raina not looking to power this one, just guides it towards sweeper cover after taking a step down the track, sends it just out of reach of point
shortish and on off stump, solid defence from Kohli
McKay grunts as he bowls the final ball of his sixth over, full and wide outside off, Kohli drives that towards cover but can't pierce the field
pitched up and on the pads, Raina likes it there, eases this off the front foot to the midwicket boundary, well timed and this outfield is very quick
a touch shorter this time, on legstump from round the wicket, Raina shuffles across and tucks that off his hip towards deep backward square leg
from over the wicket this time, Raina looks ungainly as he works this short one outside off towards deep square leg
length ball from round the wicket, only 132kph this time, defended towards the off side
the short ball has done the job, Raina goes for the pull but that flies off the toe end of the bat towards slip, Johnson has got the breakthrough Australia brought him back for

golden duck for Yuvraj! that was 148.6 kph from Mitchell Johnson, back of a length ball just outside off, Yuvraj fishes at that one well away from his body, nicks it through to the keeper, Johnson showing again just how dangerous he is with the white ball in the subcontinent
McKay bowling his seventh over here, starts with a length ball that is defended off the front foot
shortish and wide outside off, slapped towards sweeper cover for a single, think there was two there but Dhoni sends Kohli back, Dhoni seems to be having some trouble running here
Dhoni walks down the track and tucks the ball towards midwicket
again Dhoni walks across the stumps, works the ball from outside off towards midwicket
well outside off, length ball, Dhoni shoulders arms
well outside off from McKay, Dhoni moves across towards the ball and defends it towards cover
bowls this 144kph from round the wicket, worked towards midwicket
Johnson greets Dhoni with a 147kph bouncer on leg stump, Dhoni ducks under just in time
length ball on legstump, Dhoni goes back in the crease and nudges the ball towards square leg
short of length ball angling across, Dhoni steps forward and drives that powerfully past point for four, Dhoni is off the mark
fuller and on off stump, slower one as well, pushed towards mid-off by Dhoni
quick short ball from Johnson, aimed at Dhoni's ribcage, Dhoni gets back in the crease and works the ball behind square leg
pitched up, Dhoni takes a couple of paces down the track and flicks it for an ambled single
pitched up, turns it towards midwicket, Kohli wanted to push for two, Dhoni isn't interested
full ball on middle from Faulkner, pushed back towards the bowler off the front foot
back of length ball, 130kph, just outside off, Dhoni defends it towards point
fuller and that is tapped towards mid-off off the front foot
opens the face as he guides the ball from a middle-stump line towards point
mild lbw appeal on the first ball from Doherty, from round the wicket, Dhoni was several yards down the track, that looked to be sliding down
drives it inside-out towards deep extra cover for a single
shuffles towards leg and drives that towards long-off for one more
pushed back towards the bowler
length ball on middle and off, not much turn here for Doherty, more defence to the off side
fuller and on off stump, driven towards long-off for the third single of the over
goes deep in the crease and guides that behind point for a single
full and outside off, crisply driven towards cover
outside off and that is left alone
short of length ball on middle and off, pushes it towards point, Dhoni nearly slips again as he is sent back when attempting a single
length ball on the pads, whipped towards  for a quick couple
fuller and outside off, eased towards extra cover
on the pads, Dhoni takes several paces down the track and eases the ball towards long-on, easy single
dropped, that was a very thick edge though and Haddin hasn't enough time to react, strikes his right pad , good delivery from Doherty that spins just a bit
works it to the right of the bowler
pushed back towards the bowler
opens the face as he drives that towards extra cover, end of a good over from Doherty
back of length ball on off stump, guided off the back foot towards third man
pushes this towards extra cover for a single
back of a length once more, waits in the crease for that legstump delivery, plays it to the off side
short ball and that is firmly pulled away towards deep square leg, well in control as he played that, taking care to keep the ball on the ground
defended towards midwicket by Dhoni
short of length ball on off stump, Dhoni stays in the crease and pushes that towards sweeper cover
steps down the track, but defends back towards the bowler
fuller and on middle stump, worked towards long-on for a single
length ball on legstump, Kohli goes deep in the crease and nudges this behind square leg to bring up the 100
full and outside off, Dhoni reaches for that one and squeezes that towards deep point
fuller ball on middle stump, Dhoni stretches forward to reach the pitch of the ball, defended down the track
worked towards midwicket by Dhoni to end the over
short of length ball on off stump, opens the face as he sends the ball towards deep point
short of length ball on off stump, steered towards backward point
short of length ball on the pads, easy to tap that towards square leg
a touch short and that is on leg stump, Dhoni helps that along towards deep backward square leg
solid in defence as that is pitched up by Faulkner
length ball is defended towards midwicket
length ball on middle, Dhoni again taking a couple of paces down the track, eases the ball towards long-on
solid forward-defensive towards cover
fuller ball on middle, more defence, off the middle of the bat but there's loud lbw appeal
Kohli skips down and unleashes a fierce straight drive, but Doherty manages to get a hand on that
drives it inside-out towards long-off
too short from Doherty, but he gets away with it, Dhoni slaps that towards deep point
Watson returns, on the pads, worked towards deep midwicket
powerfully struck towards sweeper cover, Dhoni's leg doesn't seem to be giving him too much trouble as he races back for the second
short ball outside off, easy leave
down the leg side, easy for Kohli to put that away, just glances that past the keeper for four
length ball outside off, guided down towards third man for a single
back of length ball outside off, defended towards point
full ball is driven towards long-on for an ambled single
sends this towards cow corner
the uber-consistent Kohli gets another half-century, waits on the back foot and chops that towards point
waits for the ball to arrive and steers the ball towards backward point
full ball on the pads, whipped behind square leg
on off and middle stump, Kohli backs away from the stumps and pokes the ball towards point
worked behind square leg for a couple, this time Dhoni seems to be limping a bit, not quite full recovered from that problem he picked up early in this innings
short and wide outside off, powered towards deep point to bring up the 50-run stand
back of a length outside off, guided towards point
length ball just outside off, defended towards cover off the front foot
short of length ball outside off, guided down towards third man for a single
shortish ball outside off, pulled away towards deep square leg
nearly gone there, Dhoni charges down thtrack and looks for the big hit towards long-on, thick inside-edge sends the ball towards short fine leg
goes well back in the crease and defends to the right of the bowler, a diving stop from Doherty
beautiful from Kohli, that inside-out shot that was such a feature of his hundred in Jaipur, making some room and lofts this on the up towards deep extra cover
defended to the off side
opens the face as he guides that towards point
length ball on middle and leg, defended to the leg side
Adam Voges starts with a juicy loopy full toss, he's really lucky that isn't put away, Kohli can only get a single towards sweeper cover
a dart this time from Voges, defended off the front foot
full and just outside off, driven towards long-off
full ball is carefully defended by Kohli
once again Voges gets away with a poor ball, that was quite short, plenty of time for Kohli to rock back and put it away, he slaps it towards deep extra cover
flatter and fuller, tapped towards midwicket
exposes the stumps as he backs away and cracks the ball towards point
the helmet comes off for Dhoni as two spinners are playing,  defended off the back foot towards mid-off
clipped off the back foot towards square leg for a single
sliding down the leg side, Kohli looking to clip that towards midwicket, misses and is hit on the pads
a firm drive towards cover off the front foot
defended towards cover for a single
way outside leg stump, worked towards midwicket, no time to come back for the second
length ball from round the wicket, stays back in the crease and tucks the ball towards square leg
well outside off, Kohli has to stretch to reach that, it wasn't too short either, still Kohli waits on the back foot and powers that past cover for four

and Maxwell has done it, the massive wicket of Kohli who is dismissed for 68, Kohli gets on the front foot initially, then gets back and looks to power the ball through off, outside off and a thin edge through to the keeper, Kohli is frustrated at having given it away, India's lower order has a big task on their hands now
worked towards square leg for a single
a single towards midwicket to end the over
Dhoni rushes down the track and eases the ball towards mid-on
short ball but Dhoni can't put it away, mistimes it back towards the bowler
softly tucks this towards midwicket for a single
short of length on the pads, worked off the pads towards square leg
zipping towards off stump, shortish ball that, helped towards extra cover off the back foot
eased it past a diving Doherty, towards long-on for a single
length ball on middle and leg, driven towards mid-on
shortish ball on middle stump, Jadeja can't get bat on it as he looks to work that to the leg side

the Johnson bouncer gets another victim, speed and aggression from Johnson, Jadeja was looking to run that down towards fine leg, hits him on the gloves and the ball loops through to Haddin, superb bowling change from Bailey to attack the new batsman
short of length and outside off, Ashwin is seriously good playing the point towards point, he stylishly sends this away off the back foot past gully for four
short ball down the leg side
shortish ball on off stump, Ashwin sways out of the line of that one
short ball once more, awkward from Ashwin as he keeps that away, off the gloves and behind square leg
pitched up, on middle and leg, driven to the right of the bowler
flat, short of length ball that is angling towards legstump, defended
turns this towards midwicket, legstump ball that Dhoni delicately places on the leg side
carefully defended from the crease
taps this back towards the bowler
guides this towards short fine leg, just one off that Doherty over
full and well outside off, slices it in front of point for four, superbly done by Dhoni, not much in terms of footwork but connects well

ooh, nearly carried all the way to the man at deep point, Dhoni seems to have decided it is time to hit out, he was looking to hit that over extra cover, sliced towards point, lands short of the man there
fuller and on middle and leg, defended back towards the bowler
slower one, 126.7kph, short of length and outside off, steered in front of point
short of length ball on legstump, not very well timed but he sends the ball towards midwicket
well-directed short ball to end the over, Dhoni ducks under it
length ball just outside off, driven towards mid-off
a bit of width, fluently cut away towards point
shortish ball just outside off, gets back in the crease and the ball is sent towards deep backward point
short of length ball on the pads, looking to whip that away towards midwicket, off the pads towards the off side
short ball, Faulkner lacks the pace of Faulkner, Ashwin isn't scared of this one, helps it along to the fine-leg boundary
driven towards mid-off to end the over
short of length ball, Dhoni charges down the track and drives towards cover
opens the face and guides the ball towards third man for a single
Dhoni looking to muscle that through the off side, bounces more than he expects and he misses out
length ball is tucked in front of square leg
opens the face as he works this away towards point
short of length ball on middle stump, defended down the track
square driven towards deep point by Ashwin
short of length ball on the pads, Dhoni not looking to muscle this, tucks this behind square leg, placed perfectly to get a boundary, and another half-century for Dhoni, an ODI all-time great
full toss well outside off, slicing it down to third man for four more
length ball well outside off, defended towards mid-off off the front foot
on the pads, slower ball, Ashwin shuffles across and looks to glance it, but off the pads, wide of Haddin for four leg-byes
length ball on off stump, an elegant drive towards mid-off
McKay sends down a slower one, only 107kph, Dhoni was looking to initially launch the ball out of the park, had to adjust to the change of pace, ends up jabbing it down the ground for a quick single
length ball on off stump, defended back towards McKay
slanting in towards the pads, Ashwin moves across towards off and whips the ball towards deep square leg
pitched up, just outside off, worked towards sweeper cover for one more
a touch shorter, outside off, dabbed towards short third man
defended towards mid-on, Ashwin is sent back as he starts for the single
Watson starts the over with a length ball that is eased towards midwicket, a diving stop from Bailey
short ball on legstump, off the glove as Ashwin looks to pull, the ball rolls towards short fine leg
an appeal for lbw, that looked pretty good from a line and length point of view, but there was a big inside-edge
Dhoni looking to whip the ball towards the leg side, misses and is hit on the pads, that was sliding down
shortish ball, pulled away towards deep backward square leg for a single
length ball heading for off stump, dropped towards cover for a quick single, the Powerplay is over
Faulkner from over the wicket, a length ball is worked towards square leg
full ball just outside off, blocked back towards the bowler
angling across Ashwin, who was looking to help the ball along to third man, he can't connect
sends this one towards deep point to bring up India's 200
back of the hand slower ball, full and outside off, Dhoni can't time it as he looks launch towards long-on, towards midwicket for a single
nicely done by Ashwin, lofts that over the infield towards sweeper cover, a controlled hit for a single
full ball on the stumps, driven towards long-on for a single
another easy single towards long-on
gets well back in the crease and works this towards square leg for a single
Dhoni takes a couple of paces down the track, but he's not in place to play the big shot, tucks this to midwicket
there's the first six of the match, it was short from Doherty, Dhoni gets the front leg out of the way and muscles it over midwicket, the crowd finds its voice

Dhoni skips down the track to get near the pitch of the ball and pounds that one to the midwicket boundary, four more, Doherty's final two deliveries go for 10 runs, he still finishes with a respectable 10-0-45-0
length ball outside off, Ashwin opens the face to guide the ball towards third man for a single
short ball, Dhoni goes for the big hit, top edges the pull and the ball rolls towards deep backward square leg, Dhoni pushes Ashwin to return for the second
this time he connects superbly with the pull, he wasn't looking to give it everything, more worried about placing it, sends this to the deep square leg boundary
slanting in towards the pads, driven towards long-on

superbly done by Ashwin, innovative batting there from the No. 8, it was another short ball from Watson, Ashwin initially wanted to stand tall and pull it away, then decides to bend his knee to get under the ball and dink it down to fine leg for four
length ball just outside off, Ashwin shuffles across and pushes it towards mid-on, too firmly to have time to get a single
he starts with a full ball on the stumps, works the ball towards square leg
140kph, pitched up and just outside off, guided towards short third man
looking to pull the slower bouncer, 129kph, Dhoni is through with the shot a touch early, bottom edge on to his body, just the single

is that a caught-behind? Ashwin was looking to dab the ball down to third man once more, it's a shot that has been very profitable for him over his career, gets a thick edge, and that is a terrific take from Haddin, leaping to his left and plucking a low chance, the umpires want to double check that it carried, Ashwin was sure it did and he walks off, it was a clean take, and a very good one as well, the best of the five he has taken today
short of length ball just outside off, defended towards point
full and quick, on middle stump, squeezed out towards short third man
Watson also sticking to the short-ball strategy, bhuvneshwar looks to chop that outside-off delivery, doesn't connect
length ball just outside off, Bhuvneshwar Kumar guides that towards deep point, he looks a better batsman than a usual No. 9
Dhoni power! that is pitched up and absolutely drilled by Dhoni for six over long-off, brutal hit that, no doubt it was going to clear the rope
short ball just outside off, helped along to deep backward square leg for a single
slanting in towards legstump, clipped towards square leg
short ball down the leg side, Dhoni looking to pull that one, bit of an edge, but enough to go wide of Haddin to the fine-leg boundary
Johnson starts his final over with his favourite weapon, Bhuvneshwar Kumar ducks under it
short of length ball around off, Bhuvneshwar does well to poke it towards point and get off strike
slower one from Johnson, 128kph, Dhoni gets it towards long-on for a single
length ball on off stump, defended towards point, two balls of Johnson to go
length ball on off stump once more, just two off this over so far, defended towards point for one more
no five-for for Johnson, but it has been a superb spell form him, he ends with 4-46, his final delivery is worked towards midwicket by Bhuvneshwar
full and wide, lashed towards mid-off by Dhoni
full and well outside off, Dhonoi has to stretch as he tries reaching that, off the bottom of the bat, the ball rolls towards cover
short of length and just outside off, great line for the tailender, Bhuvneshwar chases it and is beaten
this time Bhuvneshwar defends towards short midwicket
looks to power this full ball down the ground, can't get it past Faulkner
slower one to finish, terrific over from Faulkner, just one off it, the final ball was heading for middle stump, Bhuvneshwar has to block it
slanting down the pads, helped down to fine leg for a single
slower one from McKay, Bhuvneshwar spots it early, moves away a touch, steps down the track and launches it over mid-off
powered towards mid-off for a single, Dhoni back on strike
short ball, Dhoni looking to pull that away powerfully, he can't connect properly, off the glove I think, the ball rolls towards square leg
another slower one, Bhuvneshwar was going for the mow to midwicket, thick edge sends the ball onto his pad, rolls away to allow a single

short ball sat up for Dhoni, who uncharacteristically doesn't put it away, he got plenty of power as he flatbatted it towards long-on but not wide enough of Mitchell Johnson, just a single but Dhoni won't mind too much as it brings him back on strike
mid-off was in the circle, Dhoni was all too aware of that, he gets under that low wide full toss, slices it just over mid-off for four, Dhoni on to 98

there's the first ODI century by an Indian batsman in Mohali, Dhoni has delivered another ODI masterclass, Faulkner bowling it full and wide, Dhoni doesn't get too much on it, but enough to send it to the third-man boundary for four
sends this one towards deep square leg, Dhoni puses for the second, Bhuvneshwar just makes it in time, third umpire needed to decided
Faulkner has decided the way to bowl to Dhoni is full and very wide, Dhoni reaches out and chops that towards deep point
short ball gets another wicket, Bhiuvneshwar goes for the pull but slices that high and it ends as an easy catch to Bailey at midwicket
short of length ball on middle and leg, Vinay gets behind the line of that and defends

dropped, Watson bowls it full and wide, for once Dhoni doesn't middle it as he goes for the big hit, that hit low on the bat and slices it towards cover, Bailey has plenty of time to get under it, waits for it to arrive and spills what should have been a straightforward catch
ho ho ho, Dhoni power, one ball after being dropped, drilled between the bowler and mid-off for four, brutally struck
wide outside off
full and wide once more, Dhoni looks to power it down the ground once more, bottom hand comes off the bat as he tries the shot, the ball rolls towards mid-on, Dhoni declines the single
smashes this towards the leg side, another run declined
that's why he didn't want to turn over the strike, pitched up, Dhoni pummels that for a massive six over long-off, power-hitting at its best
much too wide from Watson, he is under immense pressure when bowling to a master finisher like Dhoni
full and wide once more, not so wide that is deemed illegal, Dhoni chips it towards sweeper cover for a single
Dhoni begins the final over with a boundary, short of length ball is slugged towards midwicket, Dhoni has galloped to 122 now
full and wide, the yorker  is squeezed out towards deep point, another single refused by Dhoni

there's the helicopter, the crowd is loving it, Australia are hating it, what a player this man is, it wa sa length ball just outside off, Dhoni waits on the back foot and absolutely clobbers that over long-on
six more for Dhoni, full from Faulkner, this time Dhoni goes over long-off, all the wieght o nthe back foot as he pounds that one for six more
lashes this one towards long-on for a single, there wasn't really a chance of getting two, but Dhoni rightly wanted to be back on strike and Vinay sacrifices his wicket

sensational finish from Dhoni, this was full and on the pads, flicked off powerfully for a four, India have gone past 300 here, Dhoni ends on 139 off 122, who would want to be a bowler when Dhoni is going bonkers like this?

inn2.comm: inswinger on length and nips back into Hughes who is crammed up for room
on length and no swing this time, Hughes stays back and defends it back to the bowler
angling away after pitching on off, Hughes defends it off the back foot
outside off this time, Hughes cuts and gets a single with a bottom edge on the off side
outside off on length and shapes away, Finch poked and missed it completely without any footwork
boundary to end the over! This one was wider outside off and Finch crashed it past point for a four
pithes it outside leg and goes down further for a wide
down leg again but Dhoni doesn't give it a try this time. It may not have been out of his reach but he stared back at Vinay after it went for four
on length on the stumps, defends it back
on leg and shaping into Hughes, he works it to deep fine leg
length ball on off with a bit of outswing, pushed towards cover
on the off side again, it was swinging away, Finch drove and a good stop at cover saves a few runs
edged but out of reach of the fielders. It was short of length, Finch was on the back foot and a thick outside edge flew to third man
on length outside off, Finch cuts and misses
Finch gets room and puts it away easily. It was short too, he didn't have to do much but stay back and drive it through the covers
outside off on length, defends it to cover
on length on off, defends it back
angled into the batsman from length on off, driven down straight to mid-on
angled in again from outside off, Finch pushes it to mid-off
outside off, Hughes stays back to drive it to cover
on length outside off, leans forward to defend it on off
wider and shorter outside off, Hughes spotted it early and hopped on his toes on the back foot to push punch it between point and extra cover for four
fuller outside off, goes down on a knee to drive it to point
short of length on middle and off, tucked on the leg side for two quick runs off the back foot
short of length outside off, hops back to defend it
big appeal but it was going down leg. It was short of length and swinging into the batsman, even struck him just outside leg on the pads
angled into the pads again, goes down leg for another leg bye
full on the stumps, Finch doesn't have to move much as he crashes it straight down the ground for four
another lbw appeal and it was going down leg again as it swung in and Australia get another leg bye after Finch missed it
short of length on leg stump, worked on the leg side
towards the leg stump, pushed on the leg side
angled into from off, defends it delicately on the leg side
slightly full outside off and it's enough for Hughes to punch it through the covers, another four
on length outside off, defends it on the off side
outside off again, Hughes stays back to defend it on off
close to the stumps on the off side, Hughes defends it again
on the pads now, nudges it to deep fine leg to keep strike
back of length on middle and leg, pushed to mid-on
big appeal as it might have struck the pad first. Length delivery on leg and heading towards the stumps, Indian players see a chance and appeal but it was too close to see if it struck pas first
pushed to mid-on from length for a single
angled into Finch from length, turned to deep backward square leg for two
angled in again from off, pushed to mid-on
on length towards off stump, driven down to long-off for a single
not a bad delivery this one but it's been put away for four! Short of length outside off, Finch stayed back and punched it through the covers for a boundary
on length on the off stump, pushed down to mid-off
on the leg stump and going down, Finch tried to flick it hard but gets a leg bye to deep fine leg
short of length on leg, runs it down the leg side fine for another four. Boundaries coming easy for Australia with these two on the crease
back of length again but moving towards off this time, defends it off the back foot
length delivery on the stumps, it kept low as Hughes stayed back and tucked it to midwicket
full outside off, driven handsomely through the covers but long-off runs to deep cover to keep it to two
edged and goes where second slip would have been for four. It was outside off and the outside edge flew right past Ashwin at first slip, well outside his reach
lbw appeal but it's going down leg again as it swung too much when it struck him on the pads
angled in towards off, pushed down the ground towards mid-on
swinging in towards the pads, flicked past midwicket for easy two
well outside off, another four from Finch's bat. It was short too and he timed it very well between extra cover and point for four, nobody moved
take one more! Short ball outside off and Hughes spotted it early to pull it to deep midwicket for four
on the off stump on length, defends it off the back foot
length delivery on off again, Hughes stays on the back foot to defend towards cover
bouncer on the leg stump and Hughes ducks. First bouncer for the over
length delivery outside off, blocked off the back foot
slightly shorter on leg and surprises Hughes with the bounce a bit, defends it on the pitch
on the off stump, stays back to push it to cover

big appeal and Virat Kohli is furious after taking a diving catch at point. It was a bouncer, Finch pulled and it lobbed towards point off the shoulder, Kohli jumped forward and caught it. Replays suggest there was no bat
angled into the stumps, defends it in the crease
length delivery on off, no movement and pushed back to the bowler
another bouncer and no bat again, went straight to Dhoni this time
on leg and goes down further for a wide
length ball around off, pushed easily down the ground for two by the time long-off gets it
length delivery on the pads, pushed to mid-on
outside off on length, bottom edge stays close to Hughes who says no for the single
fuller on off, driven down to mid-off
on the stumps on length, stays low as Hughes defends it
aimed towards the stumps again and Hughes blocks it
slightly slower on middle and off, cut late to point., first maiden of the innings
angled into the pads, run down to fine leg for a leg bye

first breakthrough, Vinay strikes! It was a length delivery outside off to Hughes, and what does he do? Edges to Dhoni in an attempt to run it down to third man. The pressure of a maiden and his strike rate might have troubled him
short ball on off, Watson defends off the back foot
bouncer around off and swinging away, Watson leaves
on length on the stumps, tucked to midwicket and he's of the mark
on length on off, defends to mid-on
inside edge goes to deep fine leg. It was well outside off but nipped in late and a drive attempted by Watson just missed the stumps
on length outside off, pushes it to cover
full and outside off, driven well but straight to mid-off
short ball and pulled away for four! It went high up in the air but had the distance too and was quite far from deep square leg
aimed at the stumps, pushed to cover this time and Raina gets a direct hit at non-striker's which nearly gave an overthrow
short of length outside off, driven down to mid-off
length ball on off, driven down to mid-off where Dhawan fumbles a bit
short ball on middle and leg, pulled to deep fine leg for a single
fuller on the stumps, flicked to deep square leg for easy two
bouncer outside off, Watson leaves and a late call from the umpire calls it a wide
through the gate! On length outside off, Watson drove, reaching out but it nipped in slightly and went right through him to Dhoni
on length on off, driven dow to mid-off
short of length around off, Watson stays back and defends it back to the bowler
short of length angled in towards the stumps, turned to mid-on
on length on off, defended back to the bowler
shorter outside off, driven down easily to long-off
on the stumps this time, pushed down to mid-on
short of length outside off, Watson cuts it late to third man
full and wide, driven to sweeper cover for one
outside off and Finch pushes it to cover
wider outside off, Finch gets a bottom edge inside the crease

umpire raises the finger! Ishant has struck even though it struck him in front of leg and may have gone down leg. He angled it in, Finch was crammed for room on the back foot and the Indian players went up for Shamsuddin to raise his finger. It was very very close, hard to say if it was hitting or missing
on length outside off, Bailey lets it go
on length outside off, defends on the off side
on length and nipping in a bit, Bailey defends to end the wicket maiden
full on leg, tucked on the leg side for one
flighted on middle and leg with some turn as Bailey defends
on leg and turn again as a thick outside edge goes square on off
on length on leg and going down as there's a futile appeal for lbw
quicker on length towards the stumps as Bailey goes back to defend
shorter on leg, turned to deep square leg off the back foot and he's off the mark
angled into the batsman from length, Bailey defends
outside off this time on length, driven to cover
full on the pads, flicked on the leg side in the air and well connected from Bailey as it goes past the rope after a bounce
on length well outside off, doesn't middle it as he sends it towards cover
nips in a bit form length outside off as Bailey pushes it to point
length ball outside off, he pushes to cover and it sent back in time for the single as Rohit got the ball in no time

Jadeja strikes too! It was flat on middle and leg and didn't quite straighten as it struck Watson's pads on the back foot. The umpire took his time to raise his finger and Watson doesn't look happy as it was going down leg after hitting him outside leg
on length on middle and leg, tucked to midwicket for one
full on leg, Bailey defends awkwardly on the leg side
full on the stumps, blocks this time
flighted and full on leg, driven down to long-off
on length on the stumps, defends it on the leg side
length ball on the stumps, turned on the leg side for one
137.1 kph, short of length outside off, Voges defends off the back foot
length ball on off, defends it back
length delivery just outside off, Voges leans forward and drives to mid-off
on length outside off again, driven on the off side
short ball on off, pulled to deep midwicket for one
full on leg, tucked on the leg side
shorter and keeps low as Voges goes back to defend
on length on the stumps, leans forward to defend it
flighted on middle, Voges comes down and turns it to long-on
on lenght on middle and leg, he goes back and turns it to deep midwicket
full on middle, driven down to long-off
flighted and full outside leg, pushed to long-on
short ball and going down leg, he can't get it past short fine leg
in the air after an edge but falls short of cover. It was on length on leg but the turn produced an outside edge
down leg again and Bailey does well to stays back and send it past short fine leg for a four with a pull
on leg, Bailey sweeps but can't connect well
flighted on off, pushed to mid-off after leaning forward
slower on the stumps, Voges turns it to deep midwicket
quicker on leg, plays it to Kohli at forward short leg
shorter on the stumps, Bailey makes room and pushes to cover
full on middle and leg, driven down to long-on
outside leg and going down but they appeal as Voges couldn't get bat on that
goes down the leg side for a wide
on length on leg, Voges comes down and turns it to deep midwicket
a wide from Yuvraj down leg as Bailey tried to sweep
on length on off, pushed to cover
sways down leg again and Bailey goes down on a knee to pull it to deep fine leg
going down leg again, hits him on the pad for a leg bye
slower on length outside off, defends towards cover
on length on middle, defends it back to the bowler
full and outside off, driven firmly straight to cover
speared down the leg side
angling into the pads, looking to work it to the leg side, but can't get it away
not giving any room at all, going with the angle, defended
blocked off the front foot, batsman trying to make room but the angle isn't giving him any
waits on the backfoot and whips it towards square leg
length ball on middle and leg, pushed to the off side for a quick single
full ball on middle, pushed firmly off the front foot to the right of the bowler
blocked towards cover for a quick single
just short of length, waits on the back foot and tucks it towards midwicket
angling into legstump once more, an inside-out push towards cover
bit of flight this time, and it isn't on middle and leg line, more on off, gives the room for the batsman to cut it away through point for four
length ball on off stump, eased towards long-off for a single
short and wide from Yuvraj, asking to be hit on a track where not much is happening for the spinners, duly put away through extra cover for four more, good over for Australia this
Jadeja drops it a bit short as he plugs away on legstump, swept away for a single
defended off the back foot to the off side
length ball on middle and leg, Jadeja getting through his overs quickly, defended off the front foot to the off side
length ball on off stump, not much turn here, bowling it quick, driven towards mid-off
blocked off the front foot towards point, just a single off this over
short of length, on middle and leg, more defence, and Jadeja now has figures of 6-0-17-1, what happened to all that dew which was supposed to cause problems?
sweeps the first ball from off stump, fine towards fine leg for a single
short of length ball  pitching outside off, Bailey tucks it towards square leg
back of a length once more, on middle and leg, defended
down towards fine leg for one more
flighted from Ashwin, and that is smashed for six, it was a nice length, Bailey gets under it and hammers it towards cow corner for the first six of the innings
defended down the track to end the over
short of length and outside off, carved towards point
defended towards the off side
sees the batsman advancing and bowls it short, blocked back towards the bowler
steps out of the crease once more, Jadeja bowls this outside off for a change, Voges can only block to the off side
reverts to his leg side line, off the pads for a legbye
short of length ball on off stump, worked off the back foot towards long-on for a single
fullish ball is swept firmly towards deep square leg, just a single as the placement isn't great
from round the wicket, a length ball is defended
blocked down the track
bit of width there, and too short, slapped behind point for four more
bowling from round the wicket, from well away from the stumps, blocked back to the bowler
Jadeja continues, bowls it flat and outside off, defended to the off side
fired in towards middle, tapped back towards the bowler
on a length around middle and off, played off the back foot towards point
uller and on middle and leg, clipped behind square leg for one more
short of length ball is driven towards long-off for another single
opens the face to guide the ball behind point for another single, ends another quiet over from Jadeja
drifts away outside off, whipped towards square leg
worked to square leg for a single
goes for the quicker one, 91kph, was much too short and is fortunate that isn't put away for four, to deep midwicket for a single
defended to the leg side
spinning away, that was well outside off and going further away, giving the room  to chop it behind point, too short as well
the regulation offbreak, nudged to the leg side for a single
Jadeja continues to bowl it flat and on legstump, defended back to the bowler
a touch shorter, and on middle, driven off the back foot towards mid-on
on the pads once more, 94kph, worked towards short fine leg
short of length ball, shortening the length as he saw the batsman come down the track, defended
driven towards extra cover for a single this time
length ball on legstump, defended off the front foot, Jadeja ends another over where hardly anything is scored

short of length ball outside off, chopped behind backward point, Ashwin puts in the dive near the rope, has he touched the boundary as he tried to save it, we'll need a few replays, looks okay to me, and to the third umpire as well
beauty from Vinay Kumar, moving away late after pitching back of a length on off stump, Voges clueless against that one, has a smile on his face after being beaten
length ball is driven firmly towards mid-on
short ball outside off, tennis-style shot as he forehands it away from well outside off towards cow corner, Voges gets on his toes to make sure he is in control of that
on middle stump this time, fuller than the previous, pushed towards midwicket
short of length, angling into the pads, clipped towards deep square leg
full ball on off stump, pushed back towards the bowler
too short and outside off, chopped towards point for four, not much room for that shot but Voges connects well
whipped towards mid-on, another dot ball
length ball on middle and leg, defended to the leg side and they sprint a single
short of length, skidding on towards leg stump, blocked off the back foot
Jadeja ends with 1 for 31 off his 10 overs, Dhoni will be happy with that, the final ball was guided towards backward point for a single
first ball is defended back towards Vinay

another lbw, short of length ball on middle, Bailey wanted to swing that to the leg side but he misses, he was struck on the back leg, how high was that? seemed to be quite tight on first look, marginal call that, would have probably taken the bails
bouncer from Vinay to welcome Maxwell
looking to swing that to the leg side, gets a couple behind square leg
short ball once more, Vinay looking to bang it in this over, went for the pull, off the glove after he went through with the shot, ball rolls over to the off side

short of length ball just outside off, oh my, what is going on here? a run-out after a major mix-up, Voges pushes it towards mid-on, he sets off for the single, Maxwell does too, but after taking about four steps, Voges has second thoughts and pauses, Maxwell is well out of the blocks by now, Dhawan pounces on the ball and Maxwell's only chance was if the throw missed, it didn't, and Australia are five down, Voges swings his bat in frustration
short of length ball just outside off, defended to the off side
short of length ball outside off, guided towards third man
short of length ball, guided down towards third man for one more
shortish ball, looks to hammer that to the leg side, the pull is badly timed, just wide of mid-on
short of length and well outside off, the typical Ishant ball, was caned towards cover, Kohli dives to his right to get a hand on that
short of length ball, another tennis shot, fiercely struck boundary, that one races past deep midwicket for four
Ashwin spins in his first ball, the conventional offspinner, worked towards square leg
length ball on middle, clipped towards deep square for a couple
down the leg side, swept firmly towards deep backward square leg for two more
towards deep midwicket this time, Voges gets to his half-century
full ball is defended towards mid-on for a single
short ball on off stump, think he was looking to get that to spin away, slapped towards cover
just outside off, length ball is pushed towards wide long-on, time enough to take two
that was a terrible delivery, midway down the pitch, sat up and an easy put away, slammed over midwicket for six
length is fine but line is poor this time, slanting down the leg side, helped along past short fine leg for four more
more average bowling (to be polite) from Kohli, half-volley on the pads, whipped away to the square-leg boundary for four more
fired down the legside, Dhoni appeals for a catch, think it hit the pad on the way through
down the leg side once more, off the pads towards square leg
full ball on middle and leg, driven towards long-on for a single
Ashwin round the wicket, flighted and full outside leg stump, driven towards mid-on
pitched up, outside leg, nudged to the leg side for a single
good reverse-sweep there from Voges, but equally good work from Ishant at backward point, saves a couple of runs
a touch short, quicker as well, powered towards midwicket for a single
the carrom ball, spinning towards the pads, a leg bye towards square leg

looks to reverse-sweep once more, down the leg side, called a wide, in fact the umpire has now changed his mind, decides that is not a wide, Shamsuddin having a horror day out there, that was a huge wide
starts with a pretty poor short ball, Haddin rightly wanted to clobber that out of the ground, can't get enough distance on that, picks out long-on, Australia lose their sixth
length ball outside off, guided towards point
pushed towards point, no run for Faulkner
back of a length and outside off, driven towards sweeper cover, Dhawan races in from the rope, keeps the batsmen down to a single
short of length angling in towards legstump, worked towards deep square leg for a couple
same length and outside off, batsman had moved away from the stumps, looks to chop that through the off side,  doesn't connect
pushed back towards the bowler, not sure the batsmen knew much about that one
thumps that shortish ball towards deep square leg
full ball outside leg stump, whipped towards midwicket
drops it short once more, pulled firmly but only a single to deep midwicket
Ashwin bowling from round the stumps keeping it outside leg and heading for the stumps, a leading edge pops back towards the bowler
final ball is turned towards square leg
drilled towards long-on for a single, Australia not finding the boundaries they desperately need
mistimed shot, a flatbatted shot sends the ball towards long-on
there's one of those boundaries, short ball is slugged over midwicket for six, power hitting from Faulkner
full ball is drilled towards long-off for a single
a full toss that should have been put away, instead Voges can only thump it back towards the bowler
full and wide outside off, Voges looking to play a cute shot towards the leg side, doesn't connect
way down the leg side, Dhoni can't collect as well, and the batsmen take a run
full ball on middle, driven towards long-on
length ball, on legstump, worked towards midwicket
length ball is driven firmly back at the bowler, hits Ashwin's hand and goes on to hit the non-striker's stumps, the third umpire is called for, Faulkner had his backfoot in though
swept towards fine leg for a couple
way outside off stump, Voges has to stretch out to get to that one, stabs it towards point
defended towards point for a single
short of length ball is clubbed towards cow corner but not enough to beat the fielder
short ball from Vinay, batsman looking to hammer the ball to the leg side, that was top edged over the keeper for a one-bounce four, streaky but Faulkner won't care
length ball outside off, hammered towards cover where the diving fielder gets a hand on it
slammed towards wide long-on for a single
short of length ball, steers this wide of the man at third man for four, nicely placed that to get Australia past 250
short of length once more, badly mistimed as he looks to power the ball, a single to mid-off
bowling from wide of the stumps, from round the stumps, fired in wide of off, pushed for a single
batsman backing away, Ashwin follows him, off the pads
short of length and that is powerfully swept to the square leg boundary for four, it was the carrom ball once more, too short from Ashwin
well outside leg and heading for the pads, Voges looks to sweep but can't connect
again off the pads as the batsman shuffles around in the crease, the legstump line from Ashwin from round the wicket isn't making it easy for Australia
fired across the stumps, looking for a big hit but he misses, and the ball misses off stump as it goes through to the keeper
full and wide, Faulkner throws the bat at that and connects well, that soars over extra cover for four, the first ball is hit for a boundary and the 50 partnership comes up

what an amazing hit that is, this was short from Ishant, sat up for Faulkner, who clobbers that to cow corner, he enjoyed that shot, it went a long way beyond the rope, 10 off the first two balls, what will Ishant serve up now? first he has to get the ball back, it went into the crowd and hasn't been returned since

superb hit from Faulkner, that was a length ball, hit me it shouted, Faulkner obliged,that is as straight as they come, over the sightscreen, and some fans in the crowd hang their heads in disappointment
goes short this time, Faulkner is swinging at everything, connects well, but only a couple to deep square leg

another six, this game has turned on its head in five deliveries, fans are stunned into silence as Faulkner  reels off another six, another short ball and that is hooked behind square leg for another six

SIX MORE, what on earth? Ishant Sharma had his critics before this game, there aren't going to be many people backing him after this, short once more, another pull, right off the middle off the bat, and that sails into the crowd once more, corwd not sure whether to be gobsmacked by this hitting from Faulkner or be thrilled by this sensational turnaround, that's Fauljner's 50 as well
on the pads, that is clipped towards short fine leg for a single, 13 need off 11
another single to short fine leg
carrom ball spinning in towards the stumps, worked behind square from one more
short of length ball outside leg, dot ball as he pushes that to the right of the bowler
swiped towards deep midwicket for one more, just four off the over
full and outside leg, whipped towards deep square leg for another single, just five from that over, who do they turn to for the final over now? nine needed off it
starts with a full toos from round the wicket on leg stump, chipped towards long-on for a single
full ball is whipped towards wide long-on, Jadeja has to race across to his right , exceptional effort there from Jadeja to save two runs

a full toss from vinay on legstump, Faulkner doesn't care about the three men in the deep, backs himself to clear them and he does, a massive hit to finish off the game, Faulkner savours the moment, what an innings from him, brought Australia back from the dead, that was frankly an awful ball from Vinay, Voges also has a huge smile on his face, and why not? plenty of people were complaining about how slowly he was going in the middle overs, hardly any one will talk about that now
